annotationA: 40S ribosomal protein S9; Structural constituent of ribosome; rRNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; mitotic spindle organization
annotationB: Translationally controlled tumor protein (Tctp) belongs to the TCTP family. It interacts with the GTPase Rheb to regulate organ growth. Tctp is required for DNA damage response and genome stability
